  "body": "<div>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Discord-7289da?style=for-the-badge&amp;logo=discord&amp;logoColor=FFFFFF&amp;labelColor=293133\" alt=\"Discord\"><a style=\"background-color: rgb(13, 13, 13); font-family: Lato, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\" href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/autorestart-londi\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Modrinth-1bd96a?style=for-the-badge&amp;logo=modrinth&amp;logoColor=FFFFFF&amp;labelColor=293133\" alt=\"Modrinth\"></a><a style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: Lato, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; background-color: rgb(13, 13, 13);\" href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/autorestart\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img src=\"https://cf.way2muchnoise.eu/title/1304593.svg?badge_style=for_the_badge\" alt=\"CurseForge Mod\"></a><a style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: Lato, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; background-color: rgb(13, 13, 13); color: #e5e5e5;\" href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/autorestart\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img src=\"http://cf.way2muchnoise.eu/1304593.svg?badge_style=for_the_badge\" alt=\"CurseForge Downloads\"></a><a style=\"font-weight: 400; font-family: Lato, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; background-color: rgb(13, 13, 13);\" href=\"https://github.com/LondonDerri/AutoRestart/blob/master/LICENSE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/License-808080?style=for-the-badge\" alt=\"License\"></a><img style=\"font-weight: 400;\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/IntellijIdea-000000?style=for-the-badge&amp;logo=intellijidea&amp;logoColor=FFFFFF&amp;labelColor=293133\" alt=\"Intellij Idea\"></p>\n</div>\n<h1><strong>AutoRestart</strong></h1>\n<p><strong>AutoRestart</strong> is a mod that adds the ability to restart your server, also watch its tps and memory usage from the maximum allocated. <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\">The mod is server-based and works only on the server!</span></p>\n<h2><strong>The mod adds:</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>the command for an emergency restart of the server</li>\n<li>the command to view the next scheduled reboot</li>\n<li>a command to view the server's tps and the memory used from the maximum allocated</li>\n</ul>",
